<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-09-14T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-09-14T04:00:00-05:00" n="335" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d335">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">767.68/319: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The High Commissioner at Constantinople</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bristol</hi></persName>)
                                <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-09-14T12:00:00+03:00"><hi rend="italic">September 14,
                                        1922—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received 5:10
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>181. Wireless just received from my chief of staff at Smyrna states city
                            is burning and that all American naturalized citizens and that women of
                            native born Americans have been evacuated to Athens on destroyer <hi rend="italic">Simpson</hi> in charge of Consul Horton. No details
                            are given.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bristol</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>